  "limitations": [
    "REPLAY cannot validate the mass-balance-vs-INDEPENDENT-counter protection (the P0 core hazard, AC-F) on historical sessions: expected_universe is emitted by the candidate-generation stage (#207/#208 instrumentation) which POSTDATES every replay session, so it is RECONSTRUCTED = entered_scan + recorded pre-floor exclusions, which makes mass-balance vacuously true. That protection is validated here ONLY by the synthetic AC-F test (deployed code returns NOT-CLEAN), and requires live accrual of the generation-stage counter for real-data confirmation.",
    "CONFIG FLOOR-MODE MISMATCH: guard keys are staged in strategy_config.shadow.json which runs buy_floor=adaptive_quantile, whereas PRODUCTION runs adaptive_mean_std (guard keys absent, correctly awaiting GO). The 07-16/17 incident occurred under production adaptive_mean_std (floor 0.561). Replay evaluated BOTH: under mean+1sigma the delta is {ATI,EME,BWXT} (matches AC-a); under q0.80 the guard still admits {ATI,EME,BWXT} but with smaller delta. IMPLICATION: live shadow accrual under the CURRENT shadow config exercises the guard against the quantile floor (q80<=scores => the relax-only min() usually degrades to status quo => few/zero OPERATIVE sessions), so live shadow accrual is a WEAK path to N_shadow=10. The faithful production-behavior evidence is the mean+1sigma replay. Recommend reaching N via an EXPANDED historical replay corpus under the production floor mode, and/or documenting the floor-mode non-equivalence in the activation record.",
    "Score-SCALE-collapse failure class (05-04/05-06 at n=43/45, floor~0.26) is NOT caught by the eligibility ledger (acknowledged gap in the memo/design; needs a separate calibrator-scale integrity check). Harmless to the guard because those sessions are n>=N0 so the small-n branch never acts; noted for completeness."
  ],
  "recommendation": "Do NOT flip the production key on this replay alone (N<10). The replay is STRONG positive evidence: the guard admits exactly {ATI,EME,BWXT} on both operative sessions, XLI/XLY (mu<0) stay vetoed, no downstream-gate bypass, no new alarm class, and the eligibility ledger correctly SUPPRESSES both synthetic and REAL failure-residue days (notably averting a 33-38 name mass-admit on the 05-12..15 mu-none inflation days). To reach GO: (a) accrue to N_shadow=10 operative affected sessions -- preferably via an expanded historical replay under the production adaptive_mean_std floor, since shadow-arm quantile accrual is a weak proxy; then (b) explicit operator authorization on the record; then (c) the pin PR restoring keys to production+golden. Neither agent may self-authorize."
